# Repro for the planner CTE-trim bug discovered while solving q51.
#
# Symptom: `engine.generate_sql(text)` emits SQL containing the literal string
# `INVALID_REFERENCE_BUG_<Missing source reference to sales.ext_sales_price>`
# (here `sales.sales_price`). Executing the SQL then fails at duckdb parse.
#
# Trigger conditions:
#   1. Two parallel cumulative-window properties at the same grain
#      (web_cume, store_cume), each derived from a per-channel filtered SUM.
#   2. The cross-channel comparison `web_cume > store_cume` is in WHERE
#      (not HAVING).
#   3. The auxiliary visible-on-this-row columns are declared as `auto`
#      (not `property <grain>`) — this version of the bug only reproduces
#      with auto. Promoting them to `property <sales.item.id,
#      sales.date.date>.x <- ...` makes the planner happy.
#
# What the planner does (see generated SQL): it builds an "uneven" CTE with
# both cumes, then a "juicy" CTE that joins uneven + a small WHERE-filter
# CTE on (item, date). juicy carries `web_cume` + `web_daily` but NOT
# `store_cume` / `store_daily`. The outer SELECT then references
# `store_cumulative` (= store_cume) and tries to re-derive it from juicy
# by re-applying `sum(case when channel='STORE' then sales_ext_sales_price …)
# over (…)` — but `sales_ext_sales_price` is also absent from juicy,
# producing the `INVALID_REFERENCE_BUG_<Missing source reference…>` marker
# inline in the rendered SQL.
#
# Workarounds (both already known):
#   - Move the comparison to HAVING (see query51.preql)
#   - Promote the visible-on-row aliases from `auto` to
#     `property <sales.item.id, sales.date.date>.…`
#
# Investigation hints:
#   - The bug is in the source-projection step that decides which columns
#     to carry through `juicy`. It correctly carries `web_cume` (referenced
#     by the WHERE filter via `uneven.web_cume`) but stops there for
#     store_cume even though the WHERE *also* references it.
#   - With `auto` aliases, web_sales_visible / store_sales_visible are
#     re-rendered inline in the outer SELECT (not materialized in juicy);
#     possibly the planner counts only one direction of the inequality
#     when deciding what's "needed downstream".
#   - dialect/base.py `safe_get_cte_value` (or the source-map builder it
#     calls into) is where the missing-reference marker is emitted.
import unified_sales as sales;

auto web_daily <- sum(sales.sales_price ? sales.sales_channel = 'WEB') by sales.item.id, sales.date.date;
auto store_daily <- sum(sales.sales_price ? sales.sales_channel = 'STORE') by sales.item.id, sales.date.date;

property <sales.item.id, sales.date.date>.web_cume <- sum web_daily over sales.item.id order by sales.date.date asc;
property <sales.item.id, sales.date.date>.store_cume <- sum store_daily over sales.item.id order by sales.date.date asc;

# `auto` form is part of the trigger — promoting these to
# `property <sales.item.id, sales.date.date>.x <- …` makes the bug vanish.
auto web_sales_visible <- case when web_daily is not null then web_cume else null end;
auto store_sales_visible <- case when store_daily is not null then store_cume else null end;

WHERE
    sales.date.month_seq between 1200 and 1211
    and sales.item.id is not null
    and sales.sales_channel in ('WEB', 'STORE')
    and web_cume > store_cume
SELECT
    sales.item.id as item_sk,
    sales.date.date as d_date,
    web_sales_visible as web_sales,
    store_sales_visible as store_sales,
    web_cume as web_cumulative,
    store_cume as store_cumulative,
ORDER BY
    item_sk asc nulls first,
    d_date asc nulls first
LIMIT 100;
